Here's a **tabular comparison** based on the key metrics relevant to your scenario (read-only data, new data continuously flowing in, and window aggregations for analytics):  

| **Metric**            | **Parquet in S3 + DuckDB/Trino** | **Parquet in S3 + Apache Pinot** | **Materialized Views in RDS** |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------|--------------------------------|------------------------------|
| **Query Performance** | ğŸš€ Fast for large scans and aggregations (columnar storage) but may require optimization via partitioning | ğŸš€ Optimized for real-time, low-latency OLAP queries | âš ï¸ Slower for large-scale analytical queries, better suited for small aggregates |
| **Freshness of Data** | âš ï¸ Requires periodic metadata refresh (unless using Iceberg/Hudi/Delta) | ğŸš€ Real-time ingestion with Kafka or batch ingestion | âš ï¸ Refresh needs to be scheduled; delays depend on refresh strategy |
| **Scalability** | ğŸš€ Scales well, limited by S3 and query engine resources | ğŸš€ Highly scalable with distributed architecture | âš ï¸ Limited by RDS instance size and compute |
| **Ease of Maintenance** | âœ… Simple, requires periodic reloading of metadata | âš ï¸ More complex due to real-time ingestion setup | âœ… Easier to set up but needs careful tuning for refresh intervals |
| **Storage Costs** | ğŸ’² Very low (S3 storage is cheap, no always-on compute needed) | ğŸ’² Higher due to Pinotâ€™s real-time node and indexing overhead | ğŸ’² High (RDS storage and compute can get expensive) |
| **Compute Costs** | ğŸ’² Cost-efficient (serverless querying with DuckDB, Trino) | ğŸ’² Higher due to indexing, real-time nodes | ğŸ’² High (requires a powerful RDS instance for heavy queries) |
| **Window Aggregates** | âœ… Can be handled with Trino SQL/DuckDB efficiently | âœ… Native support for window functions with low-latency results | âš ï¸ Limited performance, especially for large datasets |
| **Concurrency** | ğŸš€ High, scales with compute resources | ğŸš€ Very high, designed for concurrent queries | âš ï¸ Limited by RDS compute and connection pool |
| **Best For** | **Batch analytics, cost-effective querying on large historical data** | **Real-time analytics with low-latency queries** | **Small-scale aggregated views with transactional integrity** |

### **Final Recommendation**
- **Best Choice:** **Parquet in S3 + Apache Pinot** if you need **real-time analytics with window aggregations**.
- **Cost-effective Alternative:** **Parquet in S3 + Trino/DuckDB** if you can tolerate batch query refreshes.
- **Not Recommended:** **Materialized Views in RDS** for large-scale window aggregations due to performance constraints.

